# Smart Wardrobe - Cursor AI Rules

## Project Overview
AI-powered wardrobe management system with outfit recommendations based on a Node.js backend and React frontend.

## Tech Stack
- Backend: Node.js, Express, MongoDB, Mongoose, JWT, Multer
- Frontend: React 18, Vite, TailwindCSS, Zustand, React Router

## Commands
- Development (both): `npm run dev`
- Backend only: `npm run dev:backend`  (port 5000)
- Frontend only: `npm run dev:frontend` (port 5173)
- Seed sample data: `npm run seed`
- Install all deps (root + backend + frontend): `npm run install:all`

## Backend Conventions
- Use ES modules (`import` / `export`).
- Controllers handle HTTP req/res and return `{ success, data | message }`.
- Business logic goes into services (when they grow complex).
- Use async/await with try/catch in all controllers.
- Use `auth` middleware to protect private routes.
- Keep models in `backend/models`, routes in `backend/routes`, controllers in `backend/controllers`.

### Controller pattern
// Example outline
export const someAction = async (req, res) => {
  try {
    // logic
    res.json({ success: true, data });
  } catch (error) {
    res.status(500).json({ success: false, message: error.message });
  }
};

## Frontend Conventions
- Functional React components with hooks.
- Routing with React Router v6 in `App.jsx`.
- Global state via Zustand stores in `frontend/src/stores`.
- API calls via a shared axios instance (when introduced).
- Styling with Tailwind utility classes.

### Component pattern
// Example outline
export default function ComponentName() {
  // state, effects, handlers
  return (
    <div className="...">
      {/* UI */}
    </div>
  );
}

## API Response Format
- Success: `{ success: true, data: ... }`
- Error: `{ success: false, message: "..." }`

## AI Assistant Guidelines (for Cursor)
- When asked to "add feature X", implement both backend + frontend wiring if relevant.
- When fixing a bug, first explain root cause briefly in comments, then apply a minimal fix.
- Prefer improving existing patterns instead of introducing new ones without need.

## Files to Treat as Source of Truth
- `backend/server.js` for Express setup & routes.
- `backend/controllers/*` for API behavior.
- `frontend/src/App.jsx` for routing.
- `frontend/src/pages/*` for page-level UI.
- `frontend/src/stores/*` for global state.

## Do NOT
- Commit `.env` files (use `.env.example` as template).
- Hard-code secrets, API keys, or connection strings.

